Metadata-Version: 2.1
Name: smi_leds
Version: 2024.8.24.0
Summary: A Python3 extension to drive 8 or 16 WS2812 LED Strips with a single Raspberry Pi
Home-page: https://github.com/mayhem/smi_leds
Author: Jeremy P Bentham, Robert Kaye
Classifier: Programming Language :: Python :: 3
Classifier: Development Status :: 4 - Beta
Classifier: License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License
Classifier: Operating System :: POSIX :: Linux
License-File: LICENSE
Requires-Dist: wheel

Using the SMI memory programming interface it is possible to drive 8 or 16 WS2812 LED strips glitch-free with a single Raspberry Pi. All models of Raspberry Pis should work with this module. Full documentation and writing instructions are available on the GitHub project page.
